This system is subject to monitoring. Therefore, no expectation of privacy is to be assumed.  Individuals found performing unauthorized activities are subject to disciplinary action including criminal prosecution.      How we handle any information that we gather when you visit our web site   We collect and store only the following information about you:  The date and time that you access our site; the IP address from which you are connecting; and the parts of our site that you access. We do not use cookies on our site. We want to make it clear that we will not obtain personally-identifying information about you when you visit our site, unless you choose to provide such information to us. Except for authorized law enforcement investigations, we do not share any information we receive with any outside parties.                                                                                                                                                                                                                           Home  |                     Search  |                    Firstgov  |                    Privacy  |                     Support                                                       Support available at 1-866-EGOV ICD

Interagency Contracts Directory          This site, when fully operational, will provide an online source of searchable  information on contract vehicles intended for multiple agency use.   Vehicles to be covered will include government-wide acquisition contracts, multi-agency contracts, General Services Administration Federal Supply Schedule (FSS) contracts, including multi-agency blanket purchase agreements (BPAs) under FSS contracts, and other procurement instruments intended for multiple agency use.  Federal agencies who operate these vehicles will enter and update contract information and users will be able to search this information by various data elements to learn about the services or goods offered through these vehicles as well as the procedures required for evaluating contract holders and placing orders.    The Federal Acquisition Regulatory Council has proposed an amendment to the FAR to reflect the creation of this site. The Federal Government and the public at large are invited to submit comments on this rule  as well as the data elements that are being considered for use on this site. (For a tentative listing of data elements, see the preamble to the proposed rule)    Please reference the Proposed Rule 2001-030, Electronic Listing of Acquisition Vehicles  Available for Use by More Than One Agency for more detailed information. PAGE TITLE: Logon                                                          What you can do on this page:        You can access your TreasuryDirect account by typing in your account number and password in the respective fields and clicking the  "Enter"  button.       In addition, you are given three other options depending upon your needs:          If you mistakenly arrived at this page without having established an account, the "Open an Account" link is located on the left of the screen.     If you can't remember your password, enter your account number in the proper field and follow the "Forgot Your Password" link.     If you can't remember your account number, you can point your browser to the "Forgot Your Account Number" link.             Primary Actions          Click  "Enter"  to access the  TreasuryDirect Welcome page  upon successful logon.     Click  "Forgot Your Password?"  to view your  password reminder .     Click  "Forgot Your Account Number?"  to begin a thorough  verification process .     Click  "Open an Account"  to go to the application  Introduction page . Part 38-  Federal Supply Schedule Contracting            38.000 Scope of part.           Subpart 38.1-Federal Supply Schedule Program                 38.101 General.               Subpart 38.2-Establishing and Administering Federal Supply Schedules                 38.201 Coordination requirements.

Subpart 5.6- Publicizing Multi-Agency Use Contracts          5.601   Governmentwide database of contracts.            (a)  A Governmentwide database of contracts and other procurement instruments intended for use by multiple agencies is available via the Internet at  www.contractdirectory.gov .  This searchable database is a tool that may be used to identify existing contracts and other procurement instruments that may be used to fulfill Government needs.        (b)  The contracting activity shall-              (1)  Enter the information specified at  www.contractdirectory.gov , in accordance with the instructions on that web site, within ten days of award of a Governmentwide acquisition contract (GWAC), multi-agency contract, Federal Supply Schedule contract, or any other procurement instrument intended for use by multiple agencies, including blanket purchase agreements (BPAs) under Federal Supply Schedule contracts.          (2)  Enter the information specified at  www.contractdirectory.gov  in accordance with the instructions on that web site by October 31, 2003, for all contracts and other procurement instruments intended for use by multiple agencies that were awarded before July 24, 2003.            *       *       *       *       *       *
